9pfs is a 9P translator for GNU Hurd

This is work-in-progress, but some things are already working.

There is an old version based on libnetfs (see netfs.c), and the new one
that implements the various RPCs directly.

Example usage:

$ settrans -c /tmp/9p.io ./9pfs 9p.io
$ ls /tmp/9p.io/
9grid adm contrib dist extra lsr nix patch plan9 _sources wiki xen

Potentially, this could be used together with virtio (see virtio-9p) to
get shared directories with a host machine for a VM running GNU/Hurd.

Build with 'make', or 'make CFLAGS=-g' for debugging.

To contribute improvements, send patches to bug-hurd@gnu.org with
[PATCH 9pfs] in the subject.

9pfs is distributed under GPL v3+.
